text: Stratford High Street is a Docklands Light Railway station in Stratford, London, England. It is located on the Stratford International branch of the Docklands Light Railway, which opened on 31 August 2011. ==History== The site was the location of an earlier railway station from 1847 to 1957. This was first called Stratford Bridge and later Stratford Market. ==References== Category:Docklands Light Railway stations in the London Borough of Newham Category:1892 establishments in England
title: Stratford High Street DLR station
